This paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category as it deals with the design of rating systems for online platforms. It may also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it discusses the optimization of rating systems to better distinguish quality. Additionally, the paper may be relevant to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category as it deals with online platforms and their rating systems. The Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category may also be relevant as rating systems can be vulnerable to manipulation and fraud. Finally, the Electronic Commerce (cs.EC) sub-category may be relevant as rating systems are often used in online marketplaces.
